<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 3:01PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Widespread snow will rapidly develop over southeastern Michigan
through the late afternoon.
* Air temperatures currently range between 33-35 degrees. This
will initially limit accumulations to grassy or elevated
surfaces through 4 PM. Accumulations on roadways will be more likely
after 4 PM as temperatures drop closer to freezing and snow
rates increase.
* East winds around 20 mph with gusts to 35 mph. Highly
fluctuating visibilities to or below 1 mile are expected given
the breezy conditions.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow may lead to slippery roads particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Snow is will bring a reduction in visibility to around 1 mile
or less.
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
